        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title purple-heading">Risk Management <span>Strategies</span></h2>
            <p class="section-subtitle sensitive-text">Learn how to protect your capital while pursuing trading opportunities. Sensitive trading information requires careful consideration.</p>
            
            <div class="risk-cards">
                <div class="risk-card">
                    <div class="risk-icon">
                        <i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Position Sizing</h3>
                    <p class="sensitive-text">Never risk more than 1-2% of your capital on a single trade. This is crucial for longevity in trading.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="risk-card">
                    <div class="risk-icon">
                        <i class="fas fa-balance-scale"></i>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Risk-Reward Ratio</h3>
                    <p class="sensitive-text">Aim for at least 1:2 risk-reward ratio. For every $1 risked, target $2 or more in potential profit.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="risk-card">
                    <div class="risk-icon">
                        <i class="fas fa-stop-circle"></i>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Stop-Loss Orders</h3>
                    <p class="sensitive-text">Always use stop-loss orders to limit potential losses. This is non-negotiable for risk management.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="risk-card">
                    <div class="risk-icon">
                        <i class="fas fa-brain"></i>
                    </div>
                    <h3>Psychology Management</h3>
                    <p class="sensitive-text">Emotional control is as important as strategy. Fear and greed are traders' biggest enemies.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

